            <title>[ZOOKEEPER-3373] need change description for &quot;Single System Image&quot; guarantee in document</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/ZOOKEEPER-3373</link>
                <project id="12310801" key="ZOOKEEPER">ZooKeeper</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In website, &quot;Single System Image&quot; is &quot;A client will see the same view of the service regardless of the server that it connects to.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I want to change it to &quot;Once connected, a client will see the same view of the service even if it switchs to another server&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Because the old one is a little&#160;misleading, if cluster has a&#160;outdated follower and a normal follower, I not think a client will see the same view of&#160;the service regardless of the server that it connects to at its first connection.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
